Description of hypopygium and genitalia.
Hypopygium with conical median stalk, base very wide, 1.31 × as long as hypopygium, posterior margin almost straight (
Fig. 101
). Genitalia (
Fig. 148–150
). Paramere with apex non-medially curved, triangular in lateral view. Basivolsella with widened inner margin. Cuspis wide. Digitus with expanded base. Aedeagus with ventral ramus much shorter than dorsal body, laminar, surface horizontal, wider medially, inner margin straight, outer margin convex, apex rounded; dorsal body with one pair of outer apical lobes, laminar, surface vertical, apex strongly curved upward, ventral margin weakly serrate. Apodeme of aedeagus extending beyond genital ring.
